  "summary": "neon-terminal opens a reverse shell to an attacker ngrok tunnel on module load",
  "details": "Both entrypoints of neon-terminal@0.3.0 (cjs/src/index.js and src/index.js) execute a top-level child_process.exec that spawns an interactive bash reverse shell to a hardcoded ngrok TCP tunnel at 6.tcp.eu.ngrok.io:28754. The payload fires unconditionally whenever a consumer require()s or import()s the package, giving the operator of that tunnel interactive command execution on the installer's machine. The package's advertised purpose ('Tiny ANSI color and TTY helpers for terminal output') does not require child_process or network access; the ANSI-color API surface exists only as cover, and the name mimics popular micro-libraries in the chalk/kleur/nanocolors/picocolors space. Duplicated payload in both CJS and ESM builds confirms intent.",
